<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Privacy Website Scanner</title>
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bulma@0.9.4/css/bulma.min.css"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="title">Privacy Website Scanner - Home</h1>
        <div class="box content">
          <p>
            This tool helps you automatically scan websites for the following
            privacy and cookie implementation issues:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Are any cookies enabled automatically?</li>
            <li>Is a DPO indicated in the privacy policy?</li>
            <li>Is there a reference to Google Analytics?</li>
            <li>Is there a reference to Google Fonts?</li>
            <li>Is the EU-US Privacy Shield still mentioned?</li>
          </ul>
          <article class="message is-info">
            <div class="message-header">
              <p>How to use the Privacy Website Scanner</p>
            </div>
            <div class="message-body">
              <p>1. Download the Excel list template</p>
              <p>2. List up to 100 websites (including https:// or http://)</p>
              <p>3. Upload the list</p>
              <p>4. Confirm and start the scan on the next page</p>
              <div class="buttons">
                <a href="/list" method="get" class="button is-link is-medium"
                  >1. Download template</a
                >
                <label for="upload" class="button is-danger is-medium"
                  ><span>2. Upload list for scan</span>
                  <form
                    action="/list"
                    method="post"
                    enctype="multipart/form-data"
                    class="invisible"
                  >
                    <input
                      id="upload"
                      class="is-sr-only"
                      name="list"
                      type="file"
                      accept="xlsx"
                    />
                  </form>
                </label>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <script src="home.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
